title: [ONNX] We should not export with com.facebook domain
body_html: Right now, our ONNX exports always export with 'com.facebook' domain, but the intended semantics of this is to identify the model, not the model creator. So it's inappropriate for us to slap this domain on the models; instead it should be a configurable parameter.

body: Right now, our ONNX exports always export with 'com.facebook' domain, but the intended semantics of this is to identify the *model*, not the model creator. So it's inappropriate for us to slap this domain on the models; instead it should be a configurable parameter.
